✔️ Kompatibilität / Compatibility

[DEU]
Das Plugin ist mit Spigot und Paper ab der Version 1.16.x kompatibel. Die Nutzung der neuesten Minecraft Version wird dennoch empfohlen!

Achtung! Es wird keinen Support für ältere Versionen wie z.B. 1.8 geben. Diese Versionen sind veraltet und ein Patch zur Kompatibilität macht keinen Sinn. Fragt also nicht nach solchen Updates! Update bitte auf neuere Server Versionen!

[ENG]
The plugin is compatible with Spigot and Paper from version 1.16.x. The use of the latest Minecraft version is still recommended!

Attention! There will be no support for older versions such as 1.8. So don't ask for it! These versions are outdated and a compatibility patch makes no sense. So don't ask for such updates! Please update to newer server versions!


Installation
Download the latest .jar and upload it to your Spigot/Paper plugins/ folder
(Optional) Configure the plugin with the config file /plugins/RHSignItem/config.yml
Do one of the following:
Restart your server.
Type /sign reload
Tip: For manual reloads I recommend the plugin PlugmanX.


Permissions
RHSignItem.*
overrides all other of RHSignItem's permissions
RHSignItem.sign
players with this permission are able to sign their items with /sign
RHSignItem.unsign
players with this permission are able to remove the signature of their items with /sign delete
RHSignItem.reload
players with this permission are able to reload the plugins config with /sign reload
RHSignItem.lockitem
players with this permission are able to lock a specific item with /sign lock
RHSignItem.unlockitem
players with this permission are able to unlock a specific item with /sign unlock
RHSignItem.renameitem
players with this permission are able to rename a specific item with /renameitem

Commands & Aliases
/sign <text>
description: Signs the item in the main hand with your custom lore
aliases: [signieren]
/sign delete
description: Removes the signature of an item
aliases: [del, remove, unsign]
/sign lock
description: Locks an item for a signature
aliases: [lockitem]
/sign unlock
description: Unlocks an item for a signature
aliases: [unlockitem]
/sign reload
description: Reloads the config
aliases: [rel]
/renameitem
description: Renames the held item
aliases: [umbenennen]
